<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q24_v12" title="Q24_v12" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>La superficie frontal de un cartel rectangular se modela mediante la función <m:math><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>42</m:mn></m:math>, donde x está en metros. Se sabe que el alto del cartel es <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:math>. ¿Cuál de las siguientes expresiones puede representar el ancho del cartel, de modo que el modelo del área sea coherente con A(x)?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA"><m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:math><qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si el ancho fuera x + 7, entonces el área sería (x + 6)(x + 7) = x² + 13x + 42, y esa expresión no coincide con x² − x − 42.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB"><m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:math><qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Al multiplicar (x + 6)(x − 7) se obtiene x² − 7x + 6x − 42 = x² − x − 42, que coincide exactamente con A(x).</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC"><m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:math><qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si el ancho fuera x − 6, entonces el área sería (x + 6)(x − 6) = x² − 36, y esa expresión no coincide con x² − x − 42.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD"><m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:math><qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si el ancho fuera x + 6, entonces el área sería (x + 6)(x + 6) = x² + 12x + 36, y esa expresión no coincide con x² − x − 42.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Relacionar área, alto y ancho</strong></p>
            <p>En un rectángulo se cumple:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>área</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>alto</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>×</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>ancho</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Como el alto es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, el ancho debe satisfacer:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>A</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                    <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo>×</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>ancho</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Factorizar la expresión del área</strong></p>
            <p>Se debe factorizar:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup>
                  <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>42</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Buscamos dos números cuyo producto sea <m:math><m:mrow><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>42</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> y cuya suma sea <m:math><m:mrow><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
            <p>Esos números son <m:math><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:math> y <m:math><m:mrow><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, porque:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:mrow>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>×</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:mrow>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>42</m:mn></m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Escribir la factorización</strong></p>
            <p>Entonces:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup>
                  <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>42</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                    <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:mn>7</m:mn>
                    <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Identificar el ancho</strong></p>
            <p>Como el alto es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, el otro factor corresponde al ancho:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>ancho</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>7</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 5: Verificación</strong></p>
            <p>Comprobamos multiplicando:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                    <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:mn>7</m:mn>
                    <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup>
                  <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>7</m:mn>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>42</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup>
                  <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>42</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Coincide exactamente con <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La expresión que puede representar el ancho del cartel es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, es decir, la alternativa B.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>